modules.description: Reads a file and extracts its metadata or content as a specific type, supporting source or target path contexts. Operates on data types conforming to the DATA_READABLE interface and path representations. Used to load structured data from files while preserving metadata for processing or validation.

Reads a file and extracts its metadata using a specified extraction strategy, returning the file content and metadata as a tuple. Processes files by parsing their content into a structured type while preserving raw data. Designed for workflows requiring both file content and associated metadata in a single operation.

Provides functions to manage and execute build processes, including initializing a development environment and triggering builds. Operates with configuration files and project directories. Used to set up isolated OCaml projects and compile them efficiently.

Loads structured data from files, extracting both content and metadata using defined strategies. Supports data types implementing the DATA_READABLE interface and provides path-aware processing. Returns tuples containing file content and metadata, enabling workflows that require both structured and raw information. Can be used to parse configuration files while retaining source or target path context for further processing.
